p: It was observed that only positive control treated group associated with significant (p < 0.001) increase in renal TNF-α, IL-1β, NF-κB, and IL-6 levels compared with negative control group. Experimental groups EA 50 and EA 25 exhibited a significant reduction (p < 0.001) in renal NF-κB, TNF-α, IL-1β, and IL-6 levels compared to the toxic control group (Figures 1 and 2).
